This paper deals with the application of multispectral imaging technology to improve the accuracy of mitosis detection in breast cancer histopathology. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques for classification, which suggests that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of spectral bands and z-stack focus planes, which suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of state-of-the-art classification methods, which suggests that it could also belong to the deep learning (cs.DL) sub-category.
